Part 1: Add Slack Approval Notifications (GitHub Actions)
üéØ Goal

Notify Slack when:

Production deployment is waiting for approval

Production deployment is approved and completed

1Ô∏è‚É£ Create Slack Incoming Webhook

Go to Slack ‚Üí App Directory

Search Incoming Webhooks

Add to your workspace

Choose a channel (e.g. #deployments)

Copy the Webhook URL

2Ô∏è‚É£ Store Slack Webhook as GitHub Secret
Repo ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Secrets and variables ‚Üí Actions


Add:

Name	Value
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL	<your-webhook-url>
3Ô∏è‚É£ Update Workflow with Slack Notifications
üîπ Slack Notify Before Prod Approval

Add a job before production:

  notify-prod-approval:
    name: Notify Slack ‚Äì Prod Approval Needed
    needs: deploy-staging
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'

    steps:
      - name: Send Slack notification
        run: |
          curl -X POST -H 'Content-type: application/json' \
          --data '{"text":"üö® *Production deployment awaiting approval*\nRepo: '"${{ github.repository }}"'\nRun: '"${{ github.run_id }}"'"}' \
          ${{ secrets.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}

üîπ Update Prod Job Dependency

Modify prod job:

  deploy-prod:
    name: Deploy to Production
    needs: notify-prod-approval
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'
    environment: production

üîπ Slack Notify After Prod Deployment

Add last step inside deploy-prod:

      - name: Notify Slack ‚Äì Prod Deployed
        run: |
          curl -X POST -H 'Content-type: application/json' \
          --data '{"text":"‚úÖ *Production deployment completed successfully*"}' \
          ${{ secrets.SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}

üß† Slack Learning Points (Exam Gold)

Slack secrets must be stored securely

Webhooks work without Slack plugins

Notifications are non-blocking

Approvals are enforced by environment protection, not Slack
